Preheat your #grill{} to high. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop into
a #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{})
and pop into a bowl with the olive oil, mix and season with salt and pepper.
Zest the @lemon{1/2} and cut into wedges. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}
(stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat.
Once hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and pepper and cook until slightly softened,
~{2%minutes}. Add the @king prawns{150%g} and cook, stirring, until almost cooked,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich) and lay on a
#baking tray{} cut-side up and spread the garlic mixture on top. Add the
@smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pan with a splash of
@water{} and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} to pack instructions. Pop the
garlic bread under the grill until golden, ~{2%minutes}.

Once the rice is cooked, stir it through the prawns and chorizo with the lemon
zest and parsley. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and
opaque in the middle. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Divide the rice
between plates. Add the garlic ciabattas and top them with the tomatoes, serve
with the lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over, enjoy!